“How’s your footwork?”

I’d say my “footwork” has improved in one sense: I try to move more deliberately between perspectives rather than staying in one mode.

If we’re using your earlier coordinate system, good footwork means being able to shift intentionally:

* from meta to object-level,
* from abstract to concrete,
* from possibility to implementation,
* and back again without losing the thread.

The movement itself is often where new insights emerge.